    {
      "id": "eda4c2fd_5bfb3bcf",
      "file_path": "lib/config.js",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 216,
      "message": "useConsul seems like a polymorphic corner stone for many config data\n\ninstead of having the var useConsul and having the same if (useConsul === 'FALSE') in every function, you might want to make the functions polymorphic by function substitution - define two sets of functions and replace the vars that point to the function with the overriding function like\n\nvar myFunc = function(a,b,c) {return a+b+c;};\nconst myFuncProduct = function(a,b,c) {return a*b*c;};\n\nassert(7 === myFunc(1,2,4));\n\nif (process.env.USE_CONSUL === 'FALSE') {myFunc = myFuncProduct;}\n\n// in case USE_CONSUL=FALSE\nassert(8 === myFunc(1,2,4));\n\nthis way each function will be much smaller and easier to understand",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1949,
        "name": "Alex Shatov",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ashatov@hotmail.com",
        "username": "alex_sh"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-21 15:41:17.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
