    {
      "id": "96969e2c_b2d91c8f",
      "file_path": "lib/config.js",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 134,
      "message": "To make this work, whoever writes the Helm chart is going to have to explicitly set the variables you're proposing.  They do not come automatically from k8s. \n\nIn ONAP R4, the deployment handler is launched via Helm, and inside the container the only environment variables containing \"INVENTORY\" are\nINVENTORY_PORT_8080_TCP=tcp://10.43.181.22:8080\nINVENTORY_SERVICE_PORT_INVENTORY=8080\nINVENTORY_PORT_8080_TCP_PORT=8080\nINVENTORY_SERVICE_PORT=8080\nINVENTORY_PORT_8080_TCP_ADDR=10.43.181.22\nINVENTORY_SERVICE_HOST=10.43.181.22\nINVENTORY_PORT=tcp://10.43.181.22:8080\nINVENTORY_PORT_8080_TCP_PROTO=tcp\n\nI don't see how this approach is simpler or cleaner than what I proposed.  It's easier for the person writing the Helm chart to set environment variables in a consistent way for both CM and inventory.",
